2_7	0.119254	The patients, who were referred to an obesity clinic between 1961 and 1994, were grouped by their age and body mass index.
2_8	0.13415886	Body mass index, or BMI, is increasingly becoming the standard way of talking about obesity, since it is an easy way to compare the girth of people of different heights.
2_9	0.11516791	BMI is body fat in kilograms divided by height in meters squared.
2_10	0.19025392	According to dietary guidelines issued by the Department of Agriculture, a BMI of 25 to 29.9 is considered overweight and 30 and above is obese.
